"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, Scotty here. Bacteria act different from all the cells that you perceive around you. All the cells that you perceive around you have a nucleus that contains the DNA and protects it. So what defines each cell is the DNA. Bacteria shed and gain DNA all the time. It goes directly through the membrane wall. They have no nucleus. So it's just flowing between them all the time. And it's based on the circumstances, environment, types of calories, competition, all these different things that they change and exchange DNA. This is so important because the current DNA in the bacteria is about to switch out to something else. That's why you need to eat fermented foods because it tells your bacteria what's going on in the outside world out here, and so that it can swap out the DNA that's appropriate for the condition settings and keep your cut current and up to date and in the best functioning way it can be. Thanks, y'all. Appreciate it.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, Scotty here.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 1.92,\n      \"duration\": 1.6,\n      \"confidence\": 0.991,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.995\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.72,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.88,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 0.88,\n          \"end\": 0.96,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confiden